            <thetext>The modern theme uses black arrows for the open/close buttons in a tree.  It also has a dark blue color for the selected row of a table (and therefore of treevirtual rows).  When a row is selected in the tree, it is very difficult to see the open/close buttons.

Consider catching selection on/off events and changing the open/close button to a white arrow instead of black.  (Unlike more typical widgets, this doesn&#39;t appear that it can be done easily using the &quot;state&quot; in the appearance for this virtual widget.)</thetext>
          </long_desc>
